  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Detailed transaction information is available in the packet that generated the block.\r\nAnd with these detailed transaction information, the node was already obtained from the transaction information broadcast.\r\nSo no detailed transaction information is needed in the broadcast of the generated block.\r\nIn the broadcast of the generated block, as long as there is a transaction hash, the verification requirement can be satisfied.\r\nIf the broadcast transaction data of the generated block is compressed,\r\nThen it will greatly increase the number of transactions within the generated block.\r\nIf there is only a transactional hash within the broadcast,\r\n1M size packets can hold 50,000 transaction hash,\r\nCan increase current TPS by 500 times.",
