    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The block is not limited in storage size in Ethereum. If doesn't matter how much data you transfer along with a block, the limit is always the amount of gas that transactions can consume in total.\r\n\r\nThe gas limit itself is limited by transaction processing performance, which is mostly limited by disk IO currently. Until there are better data models, better storage handling etc, reducing network bandwidth requirements won't help scale.",
